- nodejs: it's a way to start js outside browser (server side), (it's platform enables to run js on serverside)
		* written by cc
		* build in v8(run by chrome run js)
		* event driven programing: programing style based on responding events, expected to know by callbacks, after do this then do this, it's callbacks, registe these callbacks 
		* registering event: linking callback with accalty event (then and catch) // registration operantion
		* non-blocking 
		* single thread
		* lite: 
		* uses nmp to get packages
		* 
v8: google open source, written c++, used on chrome, run js on mashine, 
- jvm: provide java platform.
